msgstr "<guilabel>Algorithme</guilabel> : choisissez l'algorithme pour la procédure de mise au point automatique :"

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk5
#: ekos-focus.docbook:800
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis role=\"bold\">HFR</emphasis>: Half Flux Radius (HFR) is the recommended measure. When a star is detected, Ekos will calculate the HFR for the star. This is the radius of an imaginary circle, centered on the star center, that encloses half the star's total flux."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk5
#: ekos-focus.docbook:805
#, no-c-format
msgid "The point of best focus corresponds to the minimum HFR."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk5
#: ekos-focus.docbook:809
#, no-c-format
msgid "<emphasis role=\"bold\">HFR Adj</emphasis>: This is an experimental feature that uses a brightness adjusted HFR calculation to take account of the fact that the HFR for brighter stars is larger than for smaller stars."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk5
#: ekos-focus.docbook:813
#, no-c-format
msgid "The algorithm adjusts the value of the measured HFR, usually upwards, so the HFRs obtained by the HFR Adj method will be higher than the measured HFR values. This does not mean that you are getting worse results by using HFR Adj, simply that the measure is different."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk5
#: ekos-focus.docbook:817
#, no-c-format
msgid "When using this Measure it is usual to get smaller error bars on the datapoints when <guilabel>Use Weights</guilabel> is selected."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk5
#: ekos-focus.docbook:820
#, no-c-format
